                  </hi> I am groom <hi rend="italic">to</hi> George Penson. I lost a brdle and 1 pair of reins; these are the reins, and I lost such a bridle.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. SLEIOH</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Has Mr. Penson many horses? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Ten; he has had these reins perhaps ten or eleven weeks; I know them by cleaning them.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18490507-name-325" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18490507-name-325" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490507-name-325" type="surname" value="SEYMOUR"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490507-name-325" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN SEYMOUR</persName>
                  </hi> I am a harness-maker. I made this bridle for Mr. George Penson.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18490507-name-326" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18490507-name-326" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490507-name-326" type="surname" value="HOLMES"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490507-name-326" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM HOLMES</persName>
                  </hi> I am a watchman. On 14th April, at a quarter-past ten o'clock at night, I found the prisoner under the platform, from which they load the goods, at the Castle and Falcon Yard, in Aldersgate-street—I sent for a policeman, when the prisoner saw him coming, he pulled the bridle out of his pocket, and threw it down; the reins were found round his body at the station.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
